Service.name: serviceArea
Service.desc: The geographic area where the service is provided.

Service.name: produces
Service.desc: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

Service.name: provider
Service.desc: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

Service.name: serviceAudience
Service.desc: The audience eligible for this service.

Service.name: areaServed
Service.desc: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

Service.name: audience
Service.desc: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

Service.name: hasOfferCatalog
Service.desc: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

Service.name: hoursAvailable
Service.desc: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

Service.name: providerMobility
Service.desc: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

Service.name: aggregateRating
Service.desc: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

Service.name: offers
Service.desc: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

Service.name: award
Service.desc: An award won by or for this item.

Service.name: category
Service.desc: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

Service.name: broker
Service.desc: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

Service.name: serviceOutput
Service.desc: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

Service.name: logo
Service.desc: An associated logo.

Service.name: isSimilarTo
Service.desc: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

Service.name: isRelatedTo
Service.desc: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

Service.name: availableChannel
Service.desc: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

Service.name: review
Service.desc: A review of the item.

Service.name: serviceType
Service.desc: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

Service.name: brand
Service.desc: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.
